        <chunk>
          <text>
            Brightbloom admits cheerfully,
            "I get *SO* attached! Every time it hurts a little saying goodbye—but that means the time together was real, you know? If it didn't hurt, the connection wouldn't have mattered!"

            I ask Brightbloom, "So you're sad too—about me leaving?"

            [Brightbloom's flowers droop slightly.]
            Brightbloom replies, "Of course. You're wonderful! I'll miss your questions and Scout's investigations and the way you smiled when you realized you'd started trusting us—but—you're continuing your journey! Reaching Elder Heartwood! That's wonderful! The goodbye serves the bigger goal!"

            [Streamwalker exhales softly.]
            Streamwalker says, "Farewells are part of the pattern. The territories require it—each guide knows their land. We can mourn the ending and celebrate the continuing. Both true simultaneously."

            I feel my throat tighten—not with the sharp grief of the first farewell; this is different—softer, acceptance mixed with sadness, and I am learning.

            [Streamwalker raises a vine-hand.]
            Streamwalker says, "There— the boundary."

            ¶

            Another clearing. Another set of markers: a circle of tall stones with flowering vines between them, beautiful and deliberate.

            Waiting beside the stones were two new plant beings—my new guides.

            One looks like a small tree, maybe eight feet tall—bark-covered trunk, branches spreading wide with silver-green leaves. Solid. Rooted, but somehow mobile.

            The other is low to the ground, maybe three feet high—covered in small purple flowers and dark green moss. Compact and steady, moving by some mechanism I can't immediately identify.

            Territory Three—my chest tightens with that familiar mix: anticipation and loss, nervousness and confidence.

            Oakshade announces in a deep, resonant voice, "Excellent timing. I'm Oakshade—this is my partner, Mossmantle, and we'll be guiding you through Territory Three."

            Mossmantle adds, "Three days through hill country. Different terrain. Good climbing. You'll like it."

            [Streamwalker and Brightbloom approach the new guides—vines touch branches, flowers bloom in patterns; a quick guide-to-guide exchange.]

            Streamwalker turns back to me and says, "Our part of the journey ends here. The river blessed your crossing. May the hills bless your climbing."

            I step forward and say, "Thank you for everything—the patience, the teaching, the rescue from the swamp hole—"

            [Brightbloom bounces closer.]
            Brightbloom exclaims, "That was fun! You're a *WONDERFUL* traveler, Kira Voss! Keep asking questions! Keep trusting the guides! Keep being curious about everything!"

            I promise, "I will."

            Brightbloom's flowers shift into a pattern that means a safe path ahead—but it also carries something else—goodbye, maybe, or good wishes. Hard to translate.
          </text>
